    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To fix this <strong>emulator-causing-an-unexpected-reset</strong> issue, one trick that seems to help is:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <em><strong>Device Manager</strong></em> (Tab)</li>\n<li>Click &quot;⋮&quot; (Three Vertical Dots)</li>\n<li>Click &quot;<em><strong>Show On Disk</strong></em>&quot;</li>\n<li>Open &quot;config.ini&quot;</li>\n<li>Change &quot;hw.gpu.mode=<em>auto</em>&quot; to &quot;hw.gpu.mode=<em>guest</em>&quot;</li>\n</ol>\n<p>(Note: This also fixes a bug where emulators sometimes <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/75429459\">inexplicably flicker</a> on some devices.)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8MJ7m0PT.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8MJ7m0PT.png\" alt=\"config.ini\" /></a></p>\n"
  } ],
